	Month = {September},
	Year = {2018},
	Journal = {Journal of the American Medical Informatics Association : JAMIA},
	ISSN = {1067-5027},
	Pages = {1248—1258},
	Abstract = {Our objective was to review the characteristics, current applications, and evaluation measures of conversational agents with unconstrained natural language input capabilities used for health-related purposes. Studies were screened by independent reviewers and Cohen's kappa measured inter-coder agreement. Patient safety was rarely evaluated in the included studies. The use of conversational agents with unconstrained natural language input capabilities for health-related purposes is an emerging field of research, where the few published studies were mainly quasi-experimental, and rarely evaluated efficacy or safety.},
